dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Tilsit, sheet H-16. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Tilsit, Germany. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from German 1:25,000. German General Staff 1914-34; Germany, 1:100,000, German General Staff, sheet 5, 1934; Lithuania, 1:25,000, German General Staff 1915-16. Lithuanian place names from Levetuvos Apgyventos Veitos Census Report, 1925. Road classification in Lithuania taken from Lietuvos Zemelapis, 1:400,000, Lithuanian General Staff, 1933. Map states location as Germany though the map actually depicts Russia.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
